Residents of the oil-city of Warri were on Friday evening thrown into panic over a fire outbreak at the tank farm of Matrix Energy Limited. The Nation gathered that the fire broke out with a shattering explosion that rocked Ifiekporo, Ubeji and other nearby communities. Although the cause the incident is yet to be ascertained, sources hinted the inferno may have resulted from loading activities at the tank farm.   Buhari arrives Daura for Sallah celebration     JJC was not a nobody     EId-el-Kabir: Use religion to do good, Buhari urgesâ€¦   However, fire service men are said to be currently battling to put out the blazing fire. Reacting to the incident, the chairman of Warri South Local Government Area, Dr. Michael Tidi, urged residents to remain calm. Tidi, while confirming that fire service men have been mobilised to the scene, assured that the flames are being contained.